HEADWORD: Hysteroepilepsy
<hw>Hys`ter*o*ep"i*lep`sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hysteria</ets> + <ets>epilepsy</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease resembling hysteria in its nature, and
characterized by the occurrence of epileptiform convulsions, which can
often be controlled or excited by pressure on the ovaries, and upon
other definite points in the body.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Hys`ter*o*ep`i*lep"tic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hysterogenic</ent>⟦br⟧
